{{!--
  Symbolic Related Topology panel — observational symbolic-grammar layer.

  This panel sits BESIDE the canonical Related Tricks list (trick-related.hbs)
  and is clearly labelled as observational/non-canonical. It surfaces tricks
  that share the current trick's mechanical topology, which may cross-cut
  the IFPA trick_family. Source: staging CSV from SYMBOLIC-GRAMMAR-2.

  Renders only when `content.symbolicRelatedTopology` is non-null (allow-listed
  flagship slugs only at Phase 1). All data is pre-shaped by the service layer.

  Per UX-SHIP-1 Phase 4 (Task B). Visually subordinate to canonical sections:
    - secondary heading level (h3 inside the wrapper section)
    - "Observational" badge in header
    - footer note explaining non-canonical status
--}}
{{#if content.symbolicEducationCtas.length}}
<aside class="symbolic-trick-ctas-block" aria-label="Educational pages for this trick">
  <span class="symbolic-trick-ctas-label">Educational</span>
  <ul class="symbolic-trick-ctas">
    {{#each content.symbolicEducationCtas}}
    <li><a href="{{href}}">{{label}} →</a></li>
    {{/each}}
  </ul>
</aside>
{{/if}}

{{#if content.symbolicRelatedTopology}}
<section class="content-section symbolic-related-topology" aria-label="Related topology tricks">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <h3>
      Related topology tricks
      <span class="symbolic-layer-badge" title="Observational symbolic-grammar layer — supplementary; does not change canonical classifications">observational</span>
    </h3>
    <p class="section-intro">{{content.symbolicRelatedTopology.reasonText}}.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="symbolic-topology-members-list">
    {{#each content.symbolicRelatedTopology.members}}
    <li>
      <a href="{{detailHref}}">{{canonicalName}}</a>
      {{#if adds}}<span class="symbolic-topology-adds">{{adds}}</span>{{/if}}
      <a class="trick-hashtag" href="{{detailHref}}">{{hashtag}}</a>
    </li>
    {{/each}}
  </ul>
  <p class="symbolic-layer-footer">Observational symbolic-grammar layer. Topology groups describe mechanical similarity and may cross-cut the IFPA trick family. Canonical relating lives in the Related Tricks section above.</p>
</section>
{{/if}}
